it.polimi.constraintcomputation.reachability.statepresence.acceptingclaim

Class AcceptingClaimStatePathChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.constraintcomputation.reachability.statepresence.acceptingclaim.AcceptingClaimStatePathChecker

  • public class AcceptingClaimStatePathChecker
extends Object
    Given the intersection builder and a set of states that can be traversed along the search, checks the destination state is reachable from a source state by crossing the set of allowed state and traversing at least a state which is accepting for the claim.
    If the destination state, is reachable from the source state source, through a path that involves only allowed states and crosses at least a state which is obtained from an accepting state of the claim, the perform method returns true.
    Author:
    Claudio Menghi
